A presiding officer in Magarini was arrested for abandoning his duties on Friday morning. Nicholas Surei, a teacher at Majenjeni Secondary School, allegedly took the ballot papers to the constituency tallying center in Mapimo polling station in Gongoni Magarini and disappeared. Efforts by IEBC officials and security officials to trace the presiding officer in charge of Kwa Ndomo polling station were futile. He switched off his phone He later switch the phone on and was ordered back at the tallying centre.Magarini OCPD Gerald Barasa confirmed Sureiâ€™s arrest. Magarini constituency returning officer Raymond Makazi said it was unlawful for a presiding officer to abandon election materials before clearance.  A majority of the voters boycotted the poll.